list.item:
Expresses deep concern over increasing acts of violence which
                                    endanger or take innocent human lives or jeopardize fundamental
                                    freedoms;

Urges states to devote their immediate attention to finding
                                    just and peaceful solutions to the underlying causes which give
                                    rise to such acts of violence;

Invites states to become parties to the existing international
                                    conventions which relate to various aspects of the problem of
                                    international terrorism;

Requests the Secretary General to transmit an analytical study
                                    of the observations of states under paragraph 7 to the ad hoc
                                    committee to be established under paragraph 9;
